SUMMARY:Spring Break Mini-Camp
DESCRIPTION:Nancy Lorenz: The Elements			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n				\n									\n				\n				\n								\n					LeUyen Pham (Vietnamese-American\, born 1973)\, The Princess in Black and the Giant Problem\, 2020. Watercolor and ink on paper © 2020 LeUyen Pham				\n							\n		\n	\n\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n\n	\n		\n\nLet’s celebrate Spring Break with a fun morning creating art!  \n\n\n\nThe theme of this one-day mini-camp will be centered around books.  \n\n\n\nInspired by our latest exhibition\, LeUyen Came Along: The Art of LeUyen Pham\, participants will learn about the illustrative art and books that LeUyen has created in her long career. \n\n\n\nSome classics you may recognize include “Vampirina Ballerina\,” “The Princess in Black\,” and “Itty-Bitty Kitty-Corn\,” and more! \n\n\n\nChildren will get to create everything from a bookmark and collage to their very own book. \n\n\n\nThis camp is for children kindergarten through fifth grade. \n\n\n\nRegistration required. \n\n\n\nMembers: $60 | General Public: $75 \n\n\n\nNot a member? Join today for discounts on camps and classes\, exclusive invites\, free reciprocal admission to the Virginia Museum of Fine Arts in Richmond\, and more. Click here to learn more and become a member.  \n\n\n\nAlong Came LeUyen: The Art of LeUyen Pham was organized by the National Center for Children’s Illustrated Literature\, Abilene\, Texas. \n\n	\n\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				Add to Calendar\n								\n			\n		\n				\n			\n				\n					\n				\n			\n			\n				Driving? Get Directions\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				Share  This!\n			\n		\n						\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				Register Now\n			\n		\n			\n	\n				\n		\n						\n				\n					\n						Date:					 \n					\n						\n							\n								\n									Feb 04\, 2027								\n								\n																											\n											May 16\, 2027
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/event/spring-break-mini-camp/
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\, United States
CATEGORIES:Children & Family,Current Events,Upcoming Events
